  "prompt": "How do I get into the Australian National University?",
  "response": "To get into the Australian National University (ANU), you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Academic Requirements:\n- Achieve strong high school or previous university grades\n- Meet the specific entry requirements for your chosen course\n- International students may need to provide English proficiency test scores (IELTS, TOEFL)\n\n2. Application Process:\n- Apply online through the ANU website or UAC (Universities Admissions Centre)\n- Choose your preferred course\n- Submit academic transcripts\n- Provide proof of English language proficiency\n- Submit any additional required documents\n\n3. Selection Criteria:\n- Your selection will be based on:\n- Academic performance\n- ATAR (Australian Tertiary Admission Rank) for domestic students\n- Equivalent international qualifications\n- Potential additional criteria for specific courses\n\n4. Undergraduate Entry:\n- Complete Year 12 or equivalent\n- Meet course-specific prerequisites\n- Achieve a competitive ATAR\n\n5. Postgraduate Entry:\n- Hold a relevant undergraduate degree\n- Meet specific course requirements\n- Provide academic references\n- Potentially submit a research proposal\n\n6. Scholarship Opportunities:\n- Check ANU scholarship options\n- Apply for relevant scholarships\n\nIt's recommended to visit the official ANU website for the most current and detailed admission requirements.",
